## 1. Organisation

### 1.1 Approach

Atomic Design — components organised by complexity and reusability.

### 1.2 Hierarchy

**Atoms** — Basic building blocks (Button, Input, Icon, Text)
- Self-contained, no dependencies on other components
- Location: `src/components/atoms/`

**Molecules** — Simple component groups (SearchBar, FormField, Card)
- Combine 2-5 atoms into functional units
- Location: `src/components/molecules/`

**Organisms** — Complex UI sections (Header, ProductList, CheckoutForm)
- Combine molecules and atoms into distinct sections
- May contain business logic
- Location: `src/components/organisms/`

**Templates** — Page-level layouts (DashboardLayout, AuthLayout)
- Define page structure without real content
- Location: `src/components/templates/`

**Pages** — Specific instances with real content
- Connect to data sources, apply templates
- Location: `src/pages/` or `app/`

### 1.3 Directory Structure

src/components/
  atoms/
    Button/
    Input/
    Icon/
  molecules/
    SearchBar/
    FormField/
  organisms/
    Header/
    ProductList/
  templates/
    DashboardLayout/

### 1.4 Placement Rules

- **New component?** Start at lowest possible level (atom if possible)
- **Uses other components?** Move up one level (atom → molecule)
- **Contains business logic?** Organism or higher
- **Reused across features?** Lives in shared components/
- **Feature-specific?** Lives in features/[name]/components/
- **Promote when** component is reused in 3+ places

### 1.5 Evidence

- `src/components/atoms/Button/` — standalone, no component imports
- `src/components/molecules/SearchBar/` — combines Input + Button atoms
- `src/components/organisms/Header/` — combines Logo, Navigation, SearchBar
```

