### 4.4 Example

```
3. Component Structure

3.1 File Organisation

Folder-per-component for all components with multiple files.

3.2 Standard Structure


Button/
  index.ts           # Barrel export
  Button.tsx         # Component implementation
  Button.module.scss # Styles (if CSS Modules)
  Button.test.tsx    # Tests
  Button.types.ts    # TypeScript types (if complex)
  Button.stories.tsx # Storybook stories (if using)

3.3 Co-location

**Always co-locate:**
- Styles (`.module.scss` or styled-components)
- Tests (`.test.tsx`)
- Types (`.types.ts` if > 10 lines)

**Optional co-location:**
- Stories (`.stories.tsx`)
- Utilities specific to component

**Never co-locate:**
- Shared utilities (use `src/utils/`)
- API calls (use `src/services/` or hooks)

3.4 Naming Conventions

- **Folders:** PascalCase matching component name (`Button/`)
- **Component files:** PascalCase (`Button.tsx`)
- **Style files:** Match component (`Button.module.scss`)
- **Test files:** Component name + `.test` (`Button.test.tsx`)
- **Props interfaces:** `[Component]Props` (`ButtonProps`)

3.5 Exports

**Barrel exports via index.ts:**

// Button/index.ts
export { Button } from './Button';
export type { ButtonProps } from './Button.types';


**Import from folder, not file:**

// Good
import { Button } from '@/components/Button';

// Avoid
import { Button } from '@/components/Button/Button';

```

